Eilish has a [[soprano]] [[Voice type|vocal range]].<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/10-new-albums-to-stream-now-rolling-stone-editors-picks-11-195582/|title=10 New Albums to Stream Now: Rolling Stone Editors' Pick|date=July 28, 2017|access-date=December 29, 2018|url-access=limited|magazine=[[Rolling Stone]]|archive-date=June 26, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190626180751/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/10-new-albums-to-stream-now-rolling-stone-editors-picks-11-195582/|url-status=live}}<br />{{cite magazine|url=https://noisey.vice.com/en_us/article/pakpy9/watch-billie-eilish-set-fire-to-a-bad-relationship-in-new-video-for-watch|magazine=[[Vice (magazine)|Vice]]|title=Watch Billie Eilish Set Fire to a Bad Relationship in New Video for "watch"|first=Avery|last=Stone|date=September 18, 2017|access-date=December 29, 2018|archive-date=April 25, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190425053112/https://noisey.vice.com/en_us/article/pakpy9/watch-billie-eilish-set-fire-to-a-bad-relationship-in-new-video-for-watch|url-status=live}}<br />{{cite web|url=https://www.crfashionbook.com/celebrity/a22790441/billie-eilish-music-interview/|title=Billie Eilish on Making Music She Wants to Make|last=Studarus|first=Laura|date=August 23, 2018|access-date=December 29, 2018|work=CR Fashion Book|archive-date=December 26, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181226035725/https://www.crfashionbook.com/celebrity/a22790441/billie-eilish-music-interview/|url-status=live}}<br />{{cite web|url=https://thecentraltrend.com/53281/opinion/reviews/billie-eilishs-new-song-come-out-and-play-is-the-beginning-of-a-new-era-for-her/|title=Billie Eilish's new song "come out and play" is the beginning of a new era for her|first=Lejla|last=Tukelija|date=November 30, 2018|access-date=December 29, 2018|work=The Central Trend|archive-date=December 30, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181230181043/https://thecentraltrend.com/53281/opinion/reviews/billie-eilishs-new-song-come-out-and-play-is-the-beginning-of-a-new-era-for-her/|url-status=live}}<br />{{cite web|url=https://www.ssense.com/en-us/editorial/music/dont-ask-billie-eilish-to-smile|title=Don't Ask Billie Eilish To Smile|first=Rebecca|last=Haithcoat|publisher=[[SSENSE]]|date=February 21, 2018|access-date=February 27, 2019|archive-date=April 10, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200410020253/https://www.ssense.com/en-us/editorial/music/dont-ask-billie-eilish-to-smile|url-status=live}}</ref> Avery Stone of ''[[Noisey]]'' described her vocals as "ethereal",<ref>{{cite web|url=https://noisey.vice.com/en_us/article/pakpy9/watch-billie-eilish-set-fire-to-a-bad-relationship-in-new-video-for-watch|work=[[Vice (magazine)|Vice]]|title=Watch Billie Eilish Set Fire to a Bad Relationship in New Video for "watch"|first=Avery|last=Stone|date=September 18, 2017|access-date=December 29, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190206224746/https://noisey.vice.com/en_us/article/pakpy9/watch-billie-eilish-set-fire-to-a-bad-relationship-in-new-video-for-watch|archive-date=February 6, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> and [[Maura Johnston]] of ''[[Rolling Stone]]'' characterized them as "whispery".<ref name="rollingstone">{{cite magazine|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/10-new-albums-to-stream-now-rolling-stone-editors-picks-11-195582/|title=10 New Albums to Stream Now: Rolling Stone Editors' Pick|date=July 28, 2017|access-date=December 29, 2018|magazine=[[Rolling Stone]]|url-access=limited|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181230130455/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/10-new-albums-to-stream-now-rolling-stone-editors-picks-11-195582/|archive-date=December 30, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> [[Doreen St. Félix]] of ''[[The New Yorker]]'' opined that she has a "husky, slurring voice that she can thin out to reedy".<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.newyorker.com/culture/cultural-comment/billie-eilish-and-the-changing-face-of-pop|title=Billie Eilish and the Changing Face of Pop|first=Doreen|last=St. Félix|author-link=Doreen St. Félix|date=April 26, 2019|access-date=April 26, 2019|magazine=[[The New Yorker]]|url-access=limited|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190426173905/https://www.newyorker.com/culture/cultural-comment/billie-eilish-and-the-changing-face-of-pop|archive-date=April 26, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> Music critic [[Robert Christgau]] wrote that while Eilish is musically and commercially pop, her brand also "reminds us how amorphous [pop] has become", describing her soprano as "too diminutive for vocal calisthenics", adding that her "playful version of teen-[[Goth subculture|goth]] angst" and "[[electro (music)|electro]]-saturated debut album" captivated a diverse audience.<ref name="Vice">{{cite web|url=https://noisey.vice.com/en_us/article/mb8e9b/robert-christgau-reviews-billie-eilishs-when-we-fall-asleep-where-do-we-go|title=Robert Christgau Reviews Billie Eilish's Teen Goth Angst|work=[[Vice (magazine)|Vice]]|date=April 26, 2019|access-date=December 30, 2019|last=Christgau|first=Robert|author-link=Robert Christgau|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190430070104/https://noisey.vice.com/en_us/article/mb8e9b/robert-christgau-reviews-billie-eilishs-when-we-fall-asleep-where-do-we-go|archive-date=April 30, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> Her music incorporates pop,<ref name="Pop music">{{cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/amp/articles/columns/pop/7736384/billie-eilish-interview-bellyache-debut-album|title=Billie Eilish Is Pop's Most Impressive 15-Year-Old|magazine=Billboard|first=Jason|last=Lipshutz|date=March 23, 2017|access-date=February 5, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190408070841/https://www.billboard.com/amp/articles/columns/pop/7736384/billie-eilish-interview-bellyache-debut-album|archive-date=April 8, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> dark pop,<ref name="AllMusic"/> [[electropop]],<ref name="AllMusic">{{cite web|url=https://www.allmusic.com/artist/billie-eilish-mn0003475903/biography|title=Billie Eilish|first=Neil Z.|last=Yeung|publisher=[[AllMusic]]|access-date=August 28, 2022|archive-date=February 12, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220212172937/https://www.allmusic.com/artist/billie-eilish-mn0003475903/biography|url-status=live}}</ref> [[emo pop]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bcgavel.com/2019/02/23/emo-pop-princess-billie-eilish-wants-you-to-be-terrified/|title=Emo-Pop Princess Billie Eilish Wants You To Be Terrified|author=CARMEN CHU|work=bcgavel|date=February 23, 2019|access-date=February 23, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190307163105/http://www.bcgavel.com/2019/02/23/emo-pop-princess-billie-eilish-wants-you-to-be-terrified/|archive-date=March 7, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> [[experimental pop]],<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://hyperallergic.com/495712/billie-eilish-when-we-all-fall-asleep-where-do-we-go/|title=Billie Eilish's Creepy, Crawly Pop|magazine=[[Hyperallergic]]|first=Lucas|last=Fagen|date=April 21, 2019|access-date=July 19, 2020|archive-date=February 29, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200229230147/https://hyperallergic.com/495712/billie-eilish-when-we-all-fall-asleep-where-do-we-go/|url-status=live}}</ref> [[goth-pop]],<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.dw.com/en/billie-eilish-from-bedroom-artist-to-queen-of-pop/a-52161397 | title=Billie Eilish: From bedroom artist to queen of pop |date=January 27, 2020 |publisher=[[Deutsche Welle]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230206094838/https://www.dw.com/en/billie-eilish-from-bedroom-artist-to-queen-of-pop/a-52161397 |archive-date=February 6, 2023 |url-status=live |access-date=January 28, 2020}}</ref> [[indie pop]],<ref name="AllMusic"/><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.standard.co.uk/insider/alist/next-billie-eilish-female-musicians-poised-for-pop-superstardom-this-summer-a4169371.html|newspaper=[[Evening Standard]]|title=Who's the next Billie Eilish? The female musicians poised for pop superstardom this summer|first=Margaret|last=Abrams|date=July 15, 2019|access-date=November 9, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191219075246/https://www.standard.co.uk/insider/alist/next-billie-eilish-female-musicians-poised-for-pop-superstardom-this-summer-a4169371.html|archive-date=December 19, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> [[teen pop]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/newsround/51500889|title=Billie Eilish: Teenage pop artist drops song No Time to Die from new James Bond film|publisher=[[BBC]]|date=February 15, 2020|access-date=July 19, 2020|archive-date=July 20, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200720032241/https://www.bbc.co.uk/newsround/51500889|url-status=live}}</ref> [[alt-pop]],<ref name="AllMusic"/><ref>{{cite web|last=White|first=Jack|title=Billie Eilish and Dermot Kennedy score Top 5 debuts on the Official Irish Singles Chart|url=https://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/billie-eilish-and-dermot-kennedy-score-top-5-debuts-on-the-official-irish-singles-chart__33743/|publisher=Official Charts Company|accessdate=August 6, 2021|date=August 6, 2021|archive-date=August 6, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210806141617/https://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/billie-eilish-and-dermot-kennedy-score-top-5-debuts-on-the-official-irish-singles-chart__33743/|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=independentaltpop>{{cite news |last1=Beaumont |first1=Mark |title=Billie Eilish review, Glastonbury 2022: History-making set is 90 minutes of noir-pop catharsis |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/music/reviews/billie-eilish-review-glastonbury-2022-b2109771.html |newspaper=[[The Independent]] |date=June 26, 2022 |access-date=October 24, 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220731140615/https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/music/reviews/billie-eilish-review-glastonbury-2022-b2109771.html |archive-date=July 31, 2022 |url-status=live}}</ref> and [[pop rock]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.masterclass.com/articles/pop-rock|title=Pop Rock Music Guide: A Brief History of Pop Rock - 2023 - MasterClass|archive-url=https://archive.today/20231002142415/https://www.masterclass.com/articles/pop-rock|archive-date=October 2, 2023|url-status=live|date=February 8, 2022|access-date=February 6, 2023}}</ref> [[Musicologist]] Jessica Holmes argued that much of Eilish's music concerns her depression.<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Holmes |first1=Jessica |date=1 December 2023 |title=Billie Eilish and the Feminist Aesthetics of Depression: White Femininity, Generation Z, and Whisper Singing |url=https://online.ucpress.edu/jams/article-abstract/76/3/785/198574/Billie-Eilish-and-the-Feminist-Aesthetics-of |journal=Journal of the American Musicological Society |volume=76 |issue=3 |pages=785–829 |doi=10.1525/jams.2023.76.3.785 |access-date=12 March 2024}}</ref>

Eilish and her brother, Finneas, collaborate on songwriting.<ref name="Steph"/><ref name="Kaplan">{{cite magazine|last1=Kaplan|first1=Ilana|title=Pop Newcomer Billie Eilish Wants to Make Sure You Never Forget Her|url=http://www.papermag.com/pop-newcomer-billie-eilish-wants-to-make-sure-you-never-forget-her-2305463278.html|magazine=Paper|date=March 16, 2017|access-date=December 10, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181211054233/http://www.papermag.com/pop-newcomer-billie-eilish-wants-to-make-sure-you-never-forget-her-2305463278.html|archive-date=December 11, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> Finneas writes for Eilish's albums, produces her music, and also performs in live shows.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.onestowatch.com/blog/premiere-qa-finneas-debuts-im-in-love|title=PREMIERE + Q&A: FINNEAS Debuts "I'm In Love Without You" & Polaroid Gallery by Billie Eilish|publisher=[[Ones to Watch]]|date=September 8, 2017|access-date=February 18, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190219130237/https://www.onestowatch.com/blog/premiere-qa-finneas-debuts-im-in-love|archive-date=February 19, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="Steph">{{cite magazine|url=https://www.clashmusic.com/features/dont-wanna-be-you-billie-eilish-interviewed|title=Don't Wanna Be You: Billie Eilish Interviewed|magazine=[[Clash (magazine)|Clash]]|first=Steph|last=Kretowicz|date=July 13, 2018|access-date=February 18, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190219133106/https://www.clashmusic.com/features/dont-wanna-be-you-billie-eilish-interviewed|archive-date=February 19, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> Eilish and Finneas "like to completely make up things and become characters" and "have songs that are really fictional".<ref name="Kaplan"/> Eilish said a number of the songs also derive from her and Finneas' experiences.<ref name="Kaplan"/> They try to write "really interesting and conversational" lyrics: "We try to say stuff that doesn't have to be that deep [...] but you say something way deeper in a certain way that makes sense, but you haven't really thought about."<ref name="Kaplan"/> Finneas has stated that when he writes for his sister, he aims to "write [songs] that I think she'll relate to and enjoy singing and empathise with the lyrics and make her own".<ref name="Atwood">{{cite magazine|url=http://atwoodmagazine.com/finneas-2018-interview/|title=Wholehearted Obsession: A Conversation with FINNEAS|magazine=Atwood Magazine|date=April 27, 2018|access-date=February 18, 2019|first=Nicole|last=Almeida|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190210222747/http://atwoodmagazine.com/finneas-2018-interview/|archive-date=February 10, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> When he writes with Eilish, he tries "to help her tell whatever story she's trying to tell, bounce ideas off of her, listen to her ideas", and use a language that fits her voice telling the story.<ref name="Atwood" />

Eilish had wanted to direct her own music videos since age 14 but was initially not given the opportunity due to lack of experience.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2019/dec/19/i-never-wanted-a-normal-life-billie-eilish-the-guardian-artist-of-2019|title='I never wanted a normal life': Billie Eilish, the Guardian artist of 2019|newspaper=The Guardian|last=Petridis|first=Alex|date=December 19, 2019|access-date=January 4, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200104164929/https://www.theguardian.com/music/2019/dec/19/i-never-wanted-a-normal-life-billie-eilish-the-guardian-artist-of-2019|archive-date=January 4, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> In 2019, she made her directorial debut with the video for her song "[[Xanny (song)|Xanny]]".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://pitchfork.com/news/billie-eilish-shares-new-video-for-xanny-watch/|title=Billie Eilish Directs Her New "xanny" Video: Watch|last=Bloom|first=Madison|date=December 5, 2019|website=[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]|url-status=live|access-date=December 5, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191205195518/https://pitchfork.com/news/billie-eilish-shares-new-video-for-xanny-watch/|archive-date=December 5, 2019}}</ref>

=== Influences ===
Eilish grew up listening to [[the Beatles]], [[Justin Bieber]], [[Green Day]],<ref>{{cite AV media|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=DfTampjlba8|title=Billie Eilish and Billie Joe Armstrong Are Big Fans of Each Other {{!}} Musicians on Musicians|access-date=December 19, 2020|via=YouTube|archive-date=March 14, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210314120303/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=DfTampjlba8|url-status=live}}</ref> [[the 1975]],<ref name="auto1">{{cite news |title=102.7 KIIS FM on TikTok |publisher=TikTok |url=https://www.tiktok.com/@1027kiisfm/video/6853294344246480133 |access-date=June 13, 2023 |archive-url=https://ghostarchive.org/archive/20231006131019/https://www.tiktok.com/@1027kiisfm/video/6853294344246480133 |archive-date=October 6, 2023 |url-status=live }}</ref> [[Arctic Monkeys]], [[Linkin Park]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sedaily.com/NewsView/1S3G19OYZL|script-title=ko:[SE★인터뷰] 빌리 아일리시 "선택의 갈림길에서..내가 뭘 원하는지 정확히 알고 있다"|trans-title=[SE★interview] Billie Eilish "At a crossroads of choice..I know exactly what I want"|last=Jeong|first=Dahoon|date=August 21, 2018|work=Seoul Economic Daily|language=ko|access-date=March 28, 2021|url-status=live|archive-date=August 26, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180826220955/http://www.sedaily.com/NewsView/1S3G19OYZL}}</ref> and [[Lana Del Rey]].<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.wmagazine.com/story/billie-eilish-new-ep/|title=Meet Billie Eilish, Pop's Terrifying 15-Year-Old Prodigy|magazine=W|date=August 14, 2017 |access-date=May 6, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200128144631/https://www.wmagazine.com/story/billie-eilish-new-ep/|archive-date=January 28, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> She has said that stumbling upon [[Aurora (singer)|Aurora]]'s "[[Runaway (Aurora song)|Runaway]]" on YouTube inspired her to pursue a music career.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.vanityfair.com/style/2018/05/billie-eilish-the-young-upstart-with-co-signs-from-lorde-and-halsey|title=Billie Eilish: The Young Upstart with Co-Signs from Lorde and Halsey|last=Smith|first=Krista|date=May 31, 2018|magazine=[[Vanity Fair (magazine)|Vanity Fair]]|url-access=limited|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200420152631/https://www.vanityfair.com/style/2018/05/billie-eilish-the-young-upstart-with-co-signs-from-lorde-and-halsey|archive-date=April 20, 2020|access-date=December 9, 2019}}</ref> [[Hip hop music|Hip hop]] is her favorite genre and biggest inspiration.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ssense.com/en-us/editorial/music/dont-ask-billie-eilish-to-smile|title=Don't Ask Billie Eilish To Smile|first=Rebecca|last=Haithcoat|publisher=[[SSENSE]]|date=February 21, 2018|access-date=February 27, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190228191942/https://www.ssense.com/en-us/editorial/music/dont-ask-billie-eilish-to-smile|archive-date=February 28, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>

She has recounted that [[Matty Healy]] was an early inspiration for her: "His show is the second show I ever went to in my life. He changed so much about who I am, how I write music."<ref name="auto1"/><ref>{{cite magazine |last1=Lynskey |first1=Dorian |date=August 2, 2018 |title=How The 1975's Matty Healy Kicked Heroin and Took the Band to New Heights |magazine=Billboard |url=https://www.billboard.com/music/features/matty-healy-the-1975-billboard-cover-story-8468029/ |access-date=June 13, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230104153912/https://www.billboard.com/music/features/matty-healy-the-1975-billboard-cover-story-8468029/ |archive-date=January 4, 2023 |url-status=live}}</ref> She has also cited [[Tyler, the Creator]], [[Childish Gambino]], and [[Avril Lavigne]] as major musical and style influences.<ref>{{cite magazine |last=Martoccio |first=Angie |title=The First Time: Billie Eilish |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/billie-eilish-first-time-video-864831/ |magazine=[[Rolling Stone]]|url-access=limited|access-date=August 15, 2019 |date=July 31, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190815013107/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/billie-eilish-first-time-video-864831/ |archive-date=August 15, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine |last1=Shoemaker |first1=Whitney |title=Billie Eilish thanks Avril Lavigne for inspiring her in wholesome photo |url=https://www.altpress.com/news/billie-eilish-meets-avril-lavigne/ |magazine=[[Alternative Press (magazine)|Alternative Press]] |access-date=January 17, 2020 |date=July 13, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200129202056/https://www.altpress.com/news/billie-eilish-meets-avril-lavigne/ |archive-date=January 29, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> Other influences include [[Adele]],<ref>{{Citation |title=Billie Eilish Interview - On Thailand, Sustainability, and Adele! | date=September 2022 |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9lnmFDOPtto |access-date=September 9, 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230322204738/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9lnmFDOPtto |archive-date=March 22, 2023 |url-status=live |via=[[YouTube]]}}</ref> [[Earl Sweatshirt]], [[James Blake (musician)|James Blake]], [[Amy Winehouse]], the [[Spice Girls]], [[Lorde]], [[Marina Diamandis|Marina and the Diamonds]], [[Britney Spears]], [[Taylor Swift]], [[Nicki Minaj]], [[XXXTentacion]], and [[Twenty One Pilots]].{{refn|<ref>{{Cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/9391977/billie-eilish-musical-inspirations|title=Here Are the Artists Who Inspired Billie Eilish Over the Years|first=Gil|last=Kaufman|date=May 28, 2020|access-date=August 30, 2020|magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|archive-date=August 2, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200802000245/https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/9391977/billie-eilish-musical-inspirations|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Weiss |first1=Haley |title=Discovery: Billie Eilish |url=https://www.interviewmagazine.com/music/discovery-billie-eilish |website=[[Interview Magazine]] |access-date=August 15, 2019 |date=February 27, 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190711202626/https://www.interviewmagazine.com/music/discovery-billie-eilish |archive-date=July 11, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=15-Year-Old Music Prodigy Billie Eilish On Influences, Inspiration And What She's Listening To RN |url=https://www.elle.com.au/culture/billie-eilish-interview-playlist-influences-inspiration-14756 |website=[[Elle (magazine)|Elle]] |access-date=August 17, 2019 |date=October 25, 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191206133234/https://www.elle.com.au/culture/billie-eilish-interview-playlist-influences-inspiration-14756 |archive-date=December 6, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BPhks1h4Vfs|title=Billie Eilish Revisits SPIN Covers of Madonna, Amy Winehouse and More|work=[[Spin (magazine)|Spin]]|via=YouTube|date=December 23, 2019|access-date=January 5, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200614050051/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BPhks1h4Vfs|archive-date=June 14, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine |last1=Aniftos |first1=Rania |title=Here's What Finneas Thinks When People Ask About 'The Next Billie Eilish' |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/9367763/finneas-the-next-billie-eilish-question |access-date=April 29, 2020 |magazine=Billboard |date=April 28, 2020 |archive-date=April 30, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200430012432/https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/9367763/finneas-the-next-billie-eilish-question |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.etonline.com/billie-eilish-hilariously-reacts-to-britney-spears-playing-her-music-149948|title=Billie Eilish Hilariously Reacts to Britney Spears Playing Her Music|work=[[Entertainment Tonight]]|last=Tailor|first=Leena|date=July 20, 2020|access-date=March 14, 2021|archive-date=March 22, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210322133714/https://www.etonline.com/billie-eilish-hilariously-reacts-to-britney-spears-playing-her-music-149948|url-status=live|quote=On the latest episode of Apple Music's Me & Dad Radio show, Eilish and her dad, Patrick, reflected on key musical influences from the singer's childhood, including Spears, Avril Lavigne, Taylor Swift and the Spice Girls (one of whom would rave about Eilish to ET years later.)}}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine|last=Daly|first=Rhian|url=https://www.nme.com/news/music/billie-eilish-thanks-women-music-industry-paved-way-billboard-woman-of-the-year-speech-2587144|title=Billie Eilish thanks women of the music industry who "paved the way" in Billboard Woman Of The Year speech|date=December 13, 2019|magazine=NME|access-date=April 5, 2021|archive-date=March 1, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210301155815/https://www.nme.com/news/music/billie-eilish-thanks-women-music-industry-paved-way-billboard-woman-of-the-year-speech-2587144|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.standard.co.uk/showbiz/celebrity-news/spice-girls-responds-to-billie-eilish-paying-tribute-to-only-mel-c-a4225111.html|title=The Spice Girls respond after Billie Eilish pays tribute to Mel C with Sporty Spice t-shirt|newspaper=[[Evening Standard]]|date=August 30, 2019|access-date=January 5, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200129201549/https://www.standard.co.uk/showbiz/celebrity-news/spice-girls-responds-to-billie-eilish-paying-tribute-to-only-mel-c-a4225111.html|archive-date=January 29, 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref>}} She has also shown appreciation for [[Paramore]] after inviting [[Hayley Williams]] to join her set during Williams's first [[Coachella (festival)|Coachella]] set to perform an acoustic version of "[[Misery Business]]" and sing "Happier Than Ever".<ref>{{Cite magazine |date=April 25, 2022 |title=Billie Eilish brings out Paramore's Hayley Williams for Misery... |url=https://www.kerrang.com/billie-eilish-brings-out-paramores-hayley-williams-for-misery-business-at-coachella/ |access-date=May 27, 2023 |magazine=Kerrang! |first=Emily |last=Carter |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230528175149/https://www.kerrang.com/billie-eilish-brings-out-paramores-hayley-williams-for-misery-business-at-coachella/ |archive-date=May 28, 2023 |url-status=live}}</ref> Eilish also named [[Rihanna]] as an inspiration for her style choices after she called fashion her "defense mechanism" during an acceptance speech.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://jezebel.com/billie-eilish-says-she-uses-fashion-as-a-defense-mechan-1835939678|title=Billie Eilish Says She Uses Fashion As a 'Defense Mechanism'|work=[[Jezebel (website)|Jezebel]]|first=Frida|last=Garza|date=June 28, 2019|access-date=July 1, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190701060547/https://jezebel.com/billie-eilish-says-she-uses-fashion-as-a-defense-mechan-1835939678|archive-date=July 1, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> She has also credited [[Damon Albarn]] for changing the way she views art and music creation.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Halperin|first1=Shirely|last2=Miller|first2=Jeff|title=Billie Eilish Brings Out Blur's Damon Albarn for Gorillaz Classic at Coachella|url=https://variety.com/2022/music/news/billie-eilish-damon-albarn-gorillaz-coachella-1235234201/|website=Variety|date=April 17, 2022|access-date=April 17, 2022|archive-date=April 17, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220417161026/https://variety.com/2022/music/news/billie-eilish-damon-albarn-gorillaz-coachella-1235234201/|url-status=live}}</ref>

Eilish has been compared in the media to Lavigne, [[Lorde]] and Del Rey,<ref>{{cite magazine |last1=Cusumano |first1=Katherine |title=Billie Eilish, Pop's 15-Year-Old Prodigy, Relishes Being a Terrifying Teen |url=https://www.wmagazine.com/story/billie-eilish-new-ep |magazine=W |date=August 14, 2017 |access-date=August 15, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190116095926/https://www.wmagazine.com/story/billie-eilish-new-ep |archive-date=January 16, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine |last1=Bassil |first1=Ryan |title=Billie Eilish and the Rise of Moody Pop |url=https://www.vice.com/en_uk/article/eveybz/billie-eilish-when-we-fall-asleep-moody-sad-pop |magazine=[[Vice (magazine)|Vice]] |access-date=August 15, 2019 |date=April 4, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190728040821/https://www.vice.com/en_uk/article/eveybz/billie-eilish-when-we-fall-asleep-moody-sad-pop |archive-date=July 28, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="youtube.com">{{cite AV media |title= Billie Eilish on Xxxtentacion "He didn't think he was Human." |via=YouTube |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vo5JXupZTK8 |access-date=September 13, 2021 |archive-date=September 28, 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210928212612/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vo5JXupZTK8|url-status= live}}</ref> the last of whom she says she does not want to be compared to, saying, "That woman has made her brand so perfect for her whole career and she shouldn't have to hear that."<ref>{{cite magazine |last1=Song |first1=Sandra |title=Billie Eilish Wants the Lana Del Rey Comparisons to Stop |url=https://www.papermag.com/billie-eilish-lana-comparison-2634271809.html?rebelltitem=2#rebelltitem2 |magazine=Paper |access-date=August 15, 2019 |date=April 10, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190815044942/https://www.papermag.com/billie-eilish-lana-comparison-2634271809.html?rebelltitem=2#rebelltitem2 |archive-date=August 15, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> Eilish said that [[Ariana Grande]]'s 2019 album ''[[Thank U, Next]]'' inspired her to continue making music.<ref>{{cite news|title=Ariana sei Dank – Billie Eilish hat wieder Lust auf Musik|newspaper=Die Zeit |url=https://www.zeit.de/news/2019-08/19/ariana-sei-dank-billie-eilish-hat-wieder-lust-auf-musik|publisher=Zeit Online|access-date=December 13, 2019|date=August 19, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200420152023/https://www.zeit.de/news/2019-08/19/ariana-sei-dank-billie-eilish-hat-wieder-lust-auf-musik|archive-date=April 20, 2020|language=de|url-status=live}}</ref>

== Public image and recognitions ==
{{Main|List of awards and nominations received by Billie Eilish}}
[[File:CoronaCapFest19-76 (50078994132) (cropped).jpg|thumb|upright=0.7|Eilish performing in November 2019 at [[Corona Capital]]]]
Eilish is the recipient [[List of awards and nominations received by Billie Eilish|of numerous awards]], including nine [[Grammy Awards]], two [[American Music Awards]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.etonline.com/billie-eilish-wins-new-artist-of-the-year-at-2019-american-music-awards-136775|title=Billie Eilish Wins New Artist of the Year at 2019 American Music Awards|work=Entertainment Tonight |last=Calvario|first=Liz|date=November 24, 2019|access-date=February 1, 2021|archive-date=January 22, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210122221632/https://www.etonline.com/billie-eilish-wins-new-artist-of-the-year-at-2019-american-music-awards-136775|url-status=live}}</ref> two [[MTV Europe Music Awards]],<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/3144137/mtv-ema-2019-winners-list/|title=EMAS 2019 MTV EMA winners: see the full list|agency=MTV News|date=November 3, 2019|last=Roth|first=Madeline|access-date=February 1, 2021|archive-date=November 3, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191103230711/http://www.mtv.com/news/3144137/mtv-ema-2019-winners-list/|url-status=live}}</ref> three [[MTV Video Music Awards]],<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://ew.com/awards/2020-mtv-vmas-winners-list/|title=2020 MTV VMA winners: See the full list|magazine=Entertainment Weekly|last=Yang|first=Rachel|date=August 30, 2020|access-date=February 1, 2021|archive-date=December 20, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201220204604/https://ew.com/awards/2020-mtv-vmas-winners-list/|url-status=live}}</ref> two [[Academy Awards]], two [[Guinness World Records]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.guinnessworldrecords.com/world-records/most-simultaneous-us-hot-100-hits-by-a-female|title=Guinness World Records: Simultaneous Hot 100s by a female|date=April 13, 2019|work=[[Guinness World Records]]|access-date=May 2, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200109124043/https://www.guinnessworldrecords.com/world-records/most-simultaneous-us-hot-100-hits-by-a-female/|archive-date=January 9, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Youngest female at No.1 on UK albums chart|url=https://www.guinnessworldrecords.com/world-records/youngest-female-at-no1-on-uk-albums-chart|date=April 5, 2019|work=[[Guinness World Records]]|access-date=May 2, 2020|archive-date=February 5, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210205014137/https://www.guinnessworldrecords.com/world-records/youngest-female-at-no1-on-uk-albums-chart|url-status=live}}</ref> three [[Brit Awards]],<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/lists/2020-brit-awards-winners-list-1276108|title=2020 Brit Awards: Billie Eilish Wins Best International Female Solo Artist|magazine=The Hollywood Reporter|date=February 18, 2020|access-date=February 1, 2021|archive-date=August 7, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200807131136/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/lists/2020-brit-awards-winners-list-1276108|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Brit Awards 2022 winners revealed as Adele and High School Musical's Olivia Rodrigo triumph|url=https://www.digitalspy.com/tv/a39014706/brit-awards-2021-winners-results/|website=Digital Spy|date=February 8, 2022 }}</ref> and three [[Billboard Music Awards|''Billboard'' Music Awards]].<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/bbmas/9465082/2020-billboard-music-awards-winners/|title=Billboard Music Awards winners|magazine=Billboard|publisher=|date=October 14, 2020|access-date=January 26, 2021|archive-date=November 26, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201126175557/https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/bbmas/9465082/2020-billboard-music-awards-winners/|url-status=live}}</ref>

She has appeared in several lists such as ''[[Rolling Stone]]''{{'s}} 2023 revision of the 200 Greatest Singers of All Time and ''[[Time (magazine)|Time]]''{{'s}} 2019 "Time 100 Next" list.<ref name=":1">{{cite magazine|title=The 200 Greatest Singers of All Time|magazine=[[Rolling Stone]]|date=January 1, 2023|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-lists/best-singers-all-time-1234642307/billie-eilish-2-1234642935/|access-date=January 13, 2023|archive-url=https://archive.today/20230518000915/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-lists/best-singers-all-time-1234642307/rosalia-4-1234642320/|archive-date=May 18, 2023|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|first=McKenna|last=Aiello|title=Camila Cabello and More Stars Among 2019 TIME 100 Next Honorees|url=https://www.eonline.com/news/1092755/camila-cabello-and-more-stars-among-2019-time-100-next-honorees|date=November 13, 2019|website=[[E! Online]]|access-date=February 16, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321003843/https://www.eonline.com/news/1092755/camila-cabello-and-more-stars-among-2019-time-100-next-honorees|archive-date=March 21, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> She is the youngest person, second person ever, and first female artist to win the four main Grammy categories—[[Grammy Award for Best New Artist|Best New Artist]], [[Grammy Award for Record of the Year|Record of the Year]], [[Grammy Award for Song of the Year|Song of the Year]], and [[Grammy Award for Album of the Year|Album of the Year]]—in the same year.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/lifestyle/kidspost/billie-eilish-sweeps-top-grammy-awards-and-becomes-youngest-artist-to-win-one/2020/01/27/5706df3c-411d-11ea-b5fc-eefa848cde99_story.html|title=Billie Eilish sweeps top Grammy awards and becomes youngest artist to win one|newspaper=The Washington Post|via=Associated Press|access-date=February 1, 2021|archive-date=February 6, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210206235323/https://www.washingtonpost.com/lifestyle/kidspost/billie-eilish-sweeps-top-grammy-awards-and-becomes-youngest-artist-to-win-one/2020/01/27/5706df3c-411d-11ea-b5fc-eefa848cde99_story.html|url-status=live}}</ref> In 2022, Eilish won the [[Academy Award for Best Original Song]] for "[[No Time to Die (song)|No Time to Die]]" from the [[List of James Bond films|James Bond]] film [[No Time to Die|of the same name]], becoming the [[List of Academy Award records|first person born in the 21st century ever to win an Academy Award in any category]], and she remains the only. With her win [[Academy Award for Best Original Song|in the same category]] in [[96th Academy Awards|2024]] for "[[What Was I Made For?]]" from ''[[Barbie (film)|Barbie]]'' (2023), she became the youngest person ever to win two [[Academy Awards]] in any category and the song became the tenth song in history to win both an Academy Award for Best Original Song and a Grammy Award for Song of the Year, the first song this century to achieve this milestone.<ref name="WhatWasIMadeFor">{{cite magazine |last=Grein |first=Paul |date=March 10, 2024 |title=Billie Eilish's 'Barbie' Ballad Becomes 10th Song to Win Both Oscar & Top Songwriting Grammy: Full List |url=https://www.billboard.com/lists/best-song-oscar-song-of-the-year-grammy-winners/ |url-status=live |access-date=March 12, 2024 |magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |archive-date=March 11, 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240311181248/https://www.billboard.com/lists/best-song-oscar-song-of-the-year-grammy-winners/ }}</ref>

=== Style ===
Much of the media attention surrounding Eilish has revolved around her fashion style, which consists primarily of baggy, oversized clothing.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Konecky |first1=Perri |title=Billie Eilish's Style Is on a Whole Other Level, So Let's Give It Up For the Queen of Cool Comfort |url=https://www.popsugar.com/fashion/Billie-Eilish-Style-45968489 |publisher=PopSugar |access-date=August 18, 2019 |date=April 3, 2019 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20190831174520/https://www.popsugar.com/fashion/Billie-Eilish-Style-45968489 |archive-date=August 31, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine |last1=Rearick |first1=Lauren |title=Billie Eilish Took an Ikea Bag and Made it Fashion |url=https://www.teenvogue.com/gallery/favorite-billie-eilish-outfits |magazine=[[Teen Vogue]] |date=October 15, 2020|access-date=August 18, 2019 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20190812215353/https://www.teenvogue.com/gallery/favorite-billie-eilish-outfits |archive-date=August 12, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name="Spencer"/> In 2017, she said she likes dressing out of her comfort zone to feel like she grabs the attention of everyone around her.<ref>{{cite magazine| first=Erica|last=Gonzales| url= https://www.harpersbazaar.com/culture/art-books-music/a13040159/billie-eilish-interview/|title=Billie Eilish Is a 15-Year-Old Pop Prodigy—And She's Intimidating as Hell|magazine=[[Harper's Bazaar]]|date=October 19, 2017|access-date=May 11, 2019|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20190501191735/https://www.harpersbazaar.com/culture/art-books-music/a13040159/billie-eilish-interview/|archive-date=May 1, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> She tries to be "really different from a lot of people" and dresses opposite to what others wear.<ref name="Kaplan"/> Aiming to "look memorable", Eilish said that she "proved to people that [she's] more important than they think" and likes being "kind of intimidating, so people will listen up."<ref name="Kaplan"/><ref name="Martin">{{cite web| url= https://www.wvtf.org/post/billie-eilish-knows-what-youre-afraid|title=Billie Eilish Knows What You're Afraid Of|publisher=[[WVTF]]|date=April 6, 2019|access-date=February 5, 2020|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20190407142046/https://www.wvtf.org/post/billie-eilish-knows-what-youre-afraid|archive-date=April 7, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Smithies|first=Grant|url=https://www.stuff.co.nz/entertainment/music/109455859/billie-eilish-musics-terrifying-teen-it-girl|title=Billie Eilish: music's 'terrifying' teen It Girl|publisher=[[Stuff (website)|Stuff]]|date=December 23, 2018|access-date=February 5, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200205205614/https://www.stuff.co.nz/entertainment/music/109455859/billie-eilish-musics-terrifying-teen-it-girl|archive-date=February 5, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> In 2019, she said: "Over time it's kind of become a thing, 'Billie Eilish, the creepy, weird, scary girl.' And I don't like that. It's lame. I just don't want to stay one thing."<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/teen-star-billie-eilish-on-therapy-her-boyfriend-and-how-fame-has-changed-her-sspcx0j00|title=Teen star Billie Eilish on therapy, her boyfriend and how fame has changed her|newspaper=[[The Times]]|first=Decca|last=Aitkenhead|date=June 29, 2019|access-date=February 5, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200204193744/https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/teen-star-billie-eilish-on-therapy-her-boyfriend-and-how-fame-has-changed-her-sspcx0j00|archive-date=February 4, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>

In May 2019, Eilish appeared in a [[Calvin Klein (company)|Calvin Klein]] advertisement, where she mentioned that she dresses in baggy clothes to prevent people from judging her body.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.teenvogue.com/story/billie-eilish-baggy-clothes-calvin-klein|title=Billie Eilish Reveals the Reason for Her Baggy Clothes in New Calvin Klein Ad|work=[[Teen Vogue]]|date=May 11, 2019|access-date=May 11, 2019|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20190512030242/https://www.teenvogue.com/story/billie-eilish-baggy-clothes-calvin-klein|archive-date=May 12, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.de/news/gxidmo/deshalb-trägt-billie-eilish-nur-weite-baggy-klamotten|title=Aus diesem Grund trägt Billie Eilish nur weite Baggy-Klamotten|publisher=[[MTV Germany]]|date=May 13, 2019|access-date=February 5, 2020|archive-url =https://web.archive.org/web/20200203200702/http://www.mtv.de/news/gxidmo/deshalb-tr%C3%A4gt-billie-eilish-nur-weite-baggy-klamotten|archive-date=February 3, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> In a March 2020 live show in Miami, as part of the Where Do We Go? Tour, she premiered ''[[Not My Responsibility]]'', a short film which addresses her experiences of body shaming.<ref name="NotMyResponsibility">{{cite magazine |last1=Shaffer |first1=Claire |title=Billie Eilish Addresses Body Shaming in Concert Interlude |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/billie-eilish-body-shaming-concert-interlude-964959/ |magazine=[[Rolling Stone]] |url-access=limited |access-date=October 14, 2020 |date=March 10, 2020 |archive-date=October 11, 2020 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20201011165438/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/billie-eilish-body-shaming-concert-interlude-964959/ |url-status=live }}</ref> ''Not My Responsibility'' was uploaded to Eilish's YouTube channel in May 2020.<ref name="ElleNMR">{{cite web |title=Billie Eilish Has Finally Released Full Film 'Not My Responsibility,' Addressing Body Shame |url=https://www.elle.com/uk/life-and-culture/a32684247/billie-eilish-not-my-responsibility-body-shame-video/ |website=[[Elle (magazine)|Elle]] |publisher=Elle |access-date=October 14, 2020 |date=May 27, 2020 |archive-date=October 9, 2020 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20201009070708/https://www.elle.com/uk/life-and-culture/a32684247/billie-eilish-not-my-responsibility-body-shame-video/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

Eilish was on the cover of the June 2021 issue of ''[[British Vogue]]''. The photoshoot by [[Craig McDean]] featured her dressed in lingerie, specifically focused on [[corsets]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vogue.co.uk/news/article/billie-eilish-vogue-cover|title=Billie Eilish Covers The June 2021 Issue Of British Vogue|first=Edward|last=Enninful|website=British Vogue|date=May 2, 2021|access-date=May 3, 2021|archive-date=May 3, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210503070245/https://www.vogue.co.uk/news/article/billie-eilish-vogue-cover|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://ca.style.yahoo.com/billie-eilish-poses-lingerie-corsets-british-vogue-body-image-171948235.html|title=Billie Eilish wears lingerie for British Vogue: 'Suddenly you're a hypocrite if you want to show your skin'|website=ca.style.yahoo.com|date=May 2, 2021 |access-date=May 3, 2021|archive-date=May 3, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210503070245/https://ca.style.yahoo.com/billie-eilish-poses-lingerie-corsets-british-vogue-body-image-171948235.html|url-status=live}}</ref> Eilish made her first appearance at the [[Met Gala]] in 2021, which had the theme "In America: A Lexicon of Fashion", wearing an [[Oscar de la Renta]] gown under the condition that the fashion house would permanently end its use of real fur.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.cbsnews.com/news/billie-eilish-oscar-de-la-renta-met-gala-fur/|title=Billie Eilish wore Oscar de la Renta at the Met Gala under one condition: They stop using fur|work=CBS News|last=O'Kane|first=Caitlin|date=September 14, 2021|access-date=September 30, 2021|archive-date=September 30, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210930160916/https://www.cbsnews.com/news/billie-eilish-oscar-de-la-renta-met-gala-fur/|url-status=live}}</ref> Though the dress was inspired by the original [[Barbie]] doll, fashion critics observed its likeness to Golden Age star [[Marilyn Monroe]], who wore a tulle de la Renta gown in the early 1950s.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.vogue.com/article/billie-eilishs-oscar-de-la-renta-met-gala-gown-is-an-ode-to-marilyn-monroe|title=Billie Eilish's Oscar de la Renta Met Gala Gown Is an Ode to Marilyn Monroe|magazine=Vogue|last=McDermott|first=Kerry|publisher=Condé Nast|date=September 16, 2021|access-date=September 30, 2021|archive-date=September 30, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210930160916/https://www.vogue.com/article/billie-eilishs-oscar-de-la-renta-met-gala-gown-is-an-ode-to-marilyn-monroe|url-status=live}}</ref>

=== Products and endorsements ===
In April 2019, Eilish released clothing in collaboration with [[Takashi Murakami]],<ref>{{cite magazine |last1=Stiegman |first1=Kelsey |title=Billie Eilish Just Dropped a Sick Clothing Collection Inspired By Her 'You Should See Me in a Crown' Video |url= https://www.seventeen.com/fashion/celeb-fashion/a27042281/billie-eilish-takashi-murakami-merch/ |magazine= Seventeen |access-date=May 27, 2019 |date=April 4, 2019 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20190505104837/https://www.seventeen.com/fashion/celeb-fashion/a27042281/billie-eilish-takashi-murakami-merch/ |archive-date=May 5, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Chin |first1=Mallory |title=Takashi Murakami & Billie Eilish Release More Collaborative Merch |url=https://hypebeast.com/2019/4/billie-eilish-takashi-murakami-merch-collab |publisher=[[Hypebeast (company)|Hypebeast]] |date=April 5, 2019 |access-date=May 27, 2019 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20190527053428/https://hypebeast.com/2019/4/billie-eilish-takashi-murakami-merch-collab |archive-date=May 27, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> inspired by her music video for "You Should See Me in a Crown", also directed and animated by Murakami, as well as a limited edition vinyl figure of herself from the video.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Li |first1=Emma |title=Watch Billie Eilish and Takashi Murakami's Music Video |url=https://vmagazine.com/article/watch-billie-eilish-and-takashi-murakamis-music-video/ |magazine=[[V (American magazine)|V]]|date=April 18, 2019 |access-date=May 27, 2019 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20190527053428/https://vmagazine.com/article/watch-billie-eilish-and-takashi-murakamis-music-video/ |archive-date=May 27, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> Eilish also collaborated with [[Adobe Creative Cloud]] the same month for a series of advertisements<ref>{{cite magazine |title=Billie Eilish x Adobe "Synesthesia" by Laundry |url=https://www.stashmedia.tv/billie-eilish-adobe-synesthesia-laundry/ |magazine=Stash |access-date=August 8, 2019 |date=June 26, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190808034836/https://www.stashmedia.tv/billie-eilish-adobe-synesthesia-laundry/ |archive-date=August 8, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> as well as a social media art contest, where users would submit artwork with the hashtag "#BILLIExADOBE".<ref>{{cite web |title=#BILLIExADOBE |url= https://makeitcenter.adobe.com/2019/04/billiexadobe_site.html |publisher=[[Adobe Creative Cloud]] |access-date=August 8, 2019 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20190808034838/https://makeitcenter.adobe.com/2019/04/billiexadobe_site.html |archive-date=August 8, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite tweet |last1=Eilish |first1=Billie |title=Billie and @CreativeCloud want you to complete a dream drawing for a chance to win $1k and meet & greet tickets to the "WHEN WE ALL FALL ASLEEP, world tour." Visit https://adobe.ly/2K0BuiJ to get started. #BILLIExADOBE #adobepartner |user=billieeilish |number=1114275262823161861 |access-date=August 8, 2019 |date=April 5, 2019 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200420151908/https://twitter.com/billieeilish/status/1114275262823161861 |archive-date=April 20, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>

Eilish appeared in the debut of Calvin Klein's #MyCalvins ad campaign in May 2019,<ref>{{cite magazine |last1=Elizabeth |first1=De |title=Billie Eilish Wears Baggy Clothes So the World Doesn't Know "Everything" About Her |url=https://www.teenvogue.com/story/billie-eilish-baggy-clothes-calvin-klein |magazine=Teen Vogue |date=May 11, 2019 |access-date=May 27, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190516203120/https://www.teenvogue.com/story/billie-eilish-baggy-clothes-calvin-klein |archive-date=May 16, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine |last1=Penrose |first1=Nerisha |title=Calvin Klein Debuts New #MyCalvins Campaign With Billie Eilish, Noah Centineo, and More |url=https://www.elle.com/culture/celebrities/a27409909/calvin-klein-mycalvins-campaign-billie-eilish-noah-centineo/ |magazine=Elle |access-date=May 27, 2019 |date=May 9, 2019 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20190527053428/https://www.elle.com/culture/celebrities/a27409909/calvin-klein-mycalvins-campaign-billie-eilish-noah-centineo/ |archive-date=May 27, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> as well as the [[Ad Council]]'s "Seize the Awkward" campaign, a series of [[public service announcements]] targeting mental health awareness.<ref>{{cite magazine |last1=Song |first1=Sandra |title=Billie Eilish Gets Candid About Coping With Her Mental Health |url=http://www.papermag.com/billie-eilish-seize-the-awkward-2637834496.html |magazine=Paper |access-date=May 27, 2019 |date=May 23, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190527053427/http://www.papermag.com/billie-eilish-seize-the-awkward-2637834496.html |archive-date=May 27, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Rettig |first1=James |title=Billie Eilish Talks Mental Health In "Seize The Awkward" PSA |url= https://www.stereogum.com/2044850/billie-eilish-mental-health-psa-seize-the-awkward/video/ |website= Stereogum |access-date=May 27, 2019 |date=May 23, 2019 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20190523180320/https://www.stereogum.com/2044850/billie-eilish-mental-health-psa-seize-the-awkward/video/ |archive-date=May 23, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> She fronted [[MCM Worldwide]]'s fall 2019 advertising campaign in July 2019,<ref>{{cite magazine |last=Burlet |first=Fleur |title=EXCLUSIVE: Billie Eilish Fronts MCM Campaign |url=https://wwd.com/fashion-news/fashion-features/billie-eilish-mcm-bad-guy-genderless-childish-major-1203220465/ |magazine=Women's Wear Daily |access-date=August 8, 2019 |date=July 17, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190717091420/https://wwd.com/fashion-news/fashion-features/billie-eilish-mcm-bad-guy-genderless-childish-major-1203220465/ |archive-date=July 17, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> and later that month collaborated with Los Angeles-based clothing brand Freak City on a clothing line.<ref>{{cite magazine |last1=Rearick |first1=Lauren |title=We Can Now Dress Like Billie Eilish |url=https://www.teenvogue.com/story/billie-eilish-capsule-collection-freak-city |magazine=Teen Vogue |date=July 22, 2019 |access-date=August 8, 2019 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20190804155314/https://www.teenvogue.com/story/billie-eilish-capsule-collection-freak-city |archive-date=August 4, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine |last1=Stiegman |first1=Kelsey |title=Billie Eilish Announces New '90s-Inspired Freak City Clothing Collection |url=https://www.seventeen.com/fashion/celeb-fashion/a28451442/billie-eilish-freak-city-clothing-collection/ |magazine=Seventeen |access-date=August 8, 2019 |date=July 19, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190808034844/https://www.seventeen.com/fashion/celeb-fashion/a28451442/billie-eilish-freak-city-clothing-collection/ |archive-date=August 8, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine |last1=Aniftos |first1=Rania |title=Billie Eilish Unveils Freak City Clothing Collaboration |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/8521007/billie-eilish-unveils-freak-city-clothing-collaboration |magazine=Billboard |date=July 18, 2019 |access-date=August 8, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190808034836/https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/8521007/billie-eilish-unveils-freak-city-clothing-collaboration |archive-date=August 8, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> Also in July 2019, she performed at a dinner hosted by [[Chanel]] on [[Shelter Island, New York|Shelter Island]] to celebrate the brand's pop-up [[yacht club]].<ref>{{cite magazine |last1=Bobb |first1=Brooke |title=Billie Eilish Shut Down Shelter Island With an Intimate Performance at The Chanel J12 Yacht Club |url=https://www.vogue.com/article/billie-eilish-chanel-j12-watch-shelter-island-sunset-beach |magazine=Vogue |date=July 22, 2019 |access-date=August 8, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190808041154/https://www.vogue.com/article/billie-eilish-chanel-j12-watch-shelter-island-sunset-beach |archive-date=August 8, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine |last=Nordstrom |first=Leigh |title=Billie Eilish Brings the Heat to Shelter Island With Chanel |url=https://wwd.com/eye/parties/chanel-j12-sunset-beach-billie-eilish-1203224388/ |magazine=Women's Wear Daily |access-date=August 8, 2019 |date=July 21, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190802201451/https://wwd.com/eye/parties/chanel-j12-sunset-beach-billie-eilish-1203224388/ |archive-date=August 2, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>

In August 2019, Eilish partnered with [[Apple Inc.|Apple]] to allow [[Apple Store]] customers to experiment with her song "[[You Should See Me in a Crown]]" in Music Lab sessions in its stores.<ref>{{cite web|last=Steeber|first=Michael|title=Billie Eilish shares creative inspiration in new Today at Apple Music Lab|url=https://9to5mac.com/2019/08/01/today-at-apple-music-remix-billie-eilish/|publisher=9to5mac.com|access-date=August 1, 2019|date=August 1, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190801192153/https://9to5mac.com/2019/08/01/today-at-apple-music-remix-billie-eilish/|archive-date=August 1, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> Eilish's collaboration with the clothing company Siberia Hills<ref>{{cite web |last1=Li |first1=Nicolaus |title=Billie Eilish & Siberia Hills Link up on an Anime-Inspired Capsule |url=https://hypebeast.com/2019/8/billie-eilish-siberia-hills-capsule-release |publisher=Hypebeast |date=August 8, 2019 |access-date=August 12, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190812215346/https://hypebeast.com/2019/8/billie-eilish-siberia-hills-capsule-release |archive-date=August 12, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine |last1=Rearick |first1=Lauren |title=Billie Eilish Designed Another Set of Streetwear Items |url=https://www.teenvogue.com/story/billie-eilish-collaborated-with-siberia-hills |magazine=Teen Vogue |date=August 8, 2019 |access-date=August 12, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190812215345/https://www.teenvogue.com/story/billie-eilish-collaborated-with-siberia-hills |archive-date=August 12, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> was met with controversy after it was revealed that the company had used plagiarized designs of [[fan art]] of the character [[Love Live! School Idol Project|Nozomi Tojo]] from ''[[Love Live! School Idol Project|Love Live!]]'', drawn by artist Makoto Kurokawa, for Eilish's clothing line.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Valdez |first1=Nick |title=Love Live! Fans Angry Over New Billie Eilish Merch Allegedly Stealing Art |url=https://comicbook.com/anime/2019/08/09/billie-eilish-siberia-hills-stolen-art-allegations-love-live/ |publisher=ComicBook.com |date=August 9, 2019 |access-date=August 12, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190812215346/https://comicbook.com/anime/2019/08/09/billie-eilish-siberia-hills-stolen-art-allegations-love-live/ |archive-date=August 12, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> The brand later clarified that Eilish had no knowledge of the plagiarism.<ref>{{cite web |last1=VanMetre |first1=Elizabeth |title=Billie Eilish's merch pulled off website after admitting to using stolen anime art |url=https://www.dailydot.com/upstream/billie-eilish-merch-stolen-anime-art/ |website=The Daily Dot |access-date=August 12, 2019 |date=August 11, 2019 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20190811234229/https://www.dailydot.com/upstream/billie-eilish-merch-stolen-anime-art/ |archive-date=August 11, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine |last1=Stiegman |first1=Kelsey |title=People Are Slamming Billie Eilish for Her Latest Merch Collab |url=https://www.seventeen.com/fashion/a28658568/billie-eilish-accused-of-stealing-art-siberia-hills-merch/ |magazine=Seventeen |access-date=August 12, 2019 |date=August 12, 2019 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20190812200751/https://www.seventeen.com/fashion/a28658568/billie-eilish-accused-of-stealing-art-siberia-hills-merch/ |archive-date=August 12, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>

In November 2021, she debuted "Eilish", her perfume brand, which is [[vegan]] and [[cruelty-free]].<ref>{{cite magazine |last1=Freund |first1=Tatjana |title=Billie Eilish Is Launching Her First Fragrance and It Smells Like Christmas |date=October 20, 2021 |url=https://www.elle.com/beauty/a37990773/billie-eilish-fragrance-launch/ |magazine=Elle |access-date=December 14, 2021 |archive-date=December 14, 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211214214920/https://www.elle.com/beauty/a37990773/billie-eilish-fragrance-launch/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine |last1=Logan |first1=Elizabeth |title=Billie Eilish Just Announced Her First Perfume |date=October 20, 2021 |url=https://www.glamour.com/story/billie-eilish-just-announced-her-first-perfume |magazine=Glamour |access-date=December 14, 2021 |archive-date=December 14, 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211214223425/https://www.glamour.com/story/billie-eilish-just-announced-her-first-perfume |url-status=live}}</ref>

== Advocacy ==
Eilish has a history of political activism, publicly expressing her views on a multitude of political issues.<ref name="Bouza-2022">{{Cite magazine |last=Bouza |first=Kat |date=July 30, 2022 |title=Watch Billie Eilish Perform Intimate Acoustic Set at Amoeba Music |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/billie-eilish-amoeba-music-acoustic-set-1390267/ |url-status=live |magazine=[[Rolling Stone]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220802023047/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/billie-eilish-amoeba-music-acoustic-set-1390267/ |archive-date=August 2, 2022 |access-date=August 4, 2022 |url-access=limited}}</ref> She has been vocal with regard to environmental causes, including [[climate change]] awareness.<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Hopper |first=Alex |date=May 3, 2022 |title=Billie Eilish Announces London Climate Change Seminar Called Overheated |url=https://americansongwriter.com/billie-eilish-announces-london-climate-change-seminar-called-overheated/ |access-date=August 28, 2022 |magazine=[[American Songwriter]] |archive-date=May 3, 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220503223008/https://americansongwriter.com/billie-eilish-announces-london-climate-change-seminar-called-overheated/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Droke |first=Carolyn |date=August 12, 2020 |title=Billie Eilish Addresses Climate Change in an Inspirational Ad Campaign |url=https://uproxx.com/pop/billie-eilish-climate-change-ad-campaign/ |access-date=August 28, 2022 |website=[[Uproxx]] |archive-date=June 4, 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220604215645/https://uproxx.com/pop/billie-eilish-climate-change-ad-campaign/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Shoaib |first=Maliha |date=June 11, 2022 |title=Can Billie Eilish Convince Fans to Shop More Sustainably? |url=https://www.voguebusiness.com/sustainability/can-billie-eilish-convince-fans-to-shop-more-sustainably |access-date=August 28, 2022 |magazine=[[Vogue (magazine)|Vogue]] |archive-date=July 6, 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220706033831/https://www.voguebusiness.com/sustainability/can-billie-eilish-convince-fans-to-shop-more-sustainably |url-status=live }}</ref> Among other pursuits, Eilish signed an open letter to world leaders urging them to take action against [[Climate change and poverty|climate-induced poverty]],<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Robinson |first=Ellie |date=May 23, 2022 |title=Coldplay, Billie Eilish, Charlie Puth and more back petition for action on poverty and climate change |url=https://www.nme.com/news/music/coldplay-billie-eilish-charlie-puth-and-more-back-petition-for-action-on-poverty-and-climate-change-3231465 |access-date=August 28, 2022 |magazine=[[NME]] |archive-date=August 28, 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220828110037/https://www.nme.com/en_asia/news/music/coldplay-billie-eilish-charlie-puth-and-more-back-petition-for-action-on-poverty-and-climate-change-3231465 |url-status=live }}</ref> embarked on an ad campaign encouraging young people to use technology for [[Environmental movement|environmental advocacy]], and hosted a six-day climate seminar in London titled Overheated to discuss topics such as [[sustainable fashion]] and [[youth activism]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Chelosky |first=Danielle |date=May 3, 2022 |title=Billie Eilish Will Host a Climate Change Seminar in London Next Month |url=https://uproxx.com/pop/billie-eilish-climate-change-seminar/ |access-date=August 28, 2022 |website=[[Uproxx]] |archive-date=August 15, 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220815115420/https://uproxx.com/pop/billie-eilish-climate-change-seminar/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Kaufman |first=Gil |date=May 3, 2022 |title=Billie Eilish and Finneas to Kick-Off London 'Overheated' Climate Event |url=https://www.billboard.com/music/pop/billie-eilish-finneas-london-overheated-climate-event-1235066074/ |access-date=August 28, 2022 |magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |archive-date=July 15, 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220715014507/https://www.billboard.com/music/pop/billie-eilish-finneas-london-overheated-climate-event-1235066074/ |url-status=live }}</ref> Her 2019 single "[[All the Good Girls Go to Hell]]" and its subsequent video center around climate change and use heaven-and-hell imagery to criticize ignorance of rising sea levels,<ref>{{Cite news |last=Hunt |first=Elle |date=September 9, 2019 |title=Is Billie Eilish a Devil Worshipper? Hell, No |url=http://www.theguardian.com/music/shortcuts/2019/sep/09/is-billie-eilish-a-devil-worshipper-hell-no |access-date=August 28, 2022 |newspaper=[[The Guardian]] |archive-date=May 19, 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220519153320/https://www.theguardian.com/music/shortcuts/2019/sep/09/is-billie-eilish-a-devil-worshipper-hell-no |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last=Pierre-Louis |first=Kendra |date=May 22, 2020 |title=The Climate 'Hot 10 Songs' |newspaper=[[The New York Times]] |url=https://www.nytimes.com/interactive/2020/05/21/climate/songs-about-climate-change.html |access-date=August 28, 2022 |archive-date=June 24, 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220624191308/https://www.nytimes.com/interactive/2020/05/21/climate/songs-about-climate-change.html |url-status=live }}</ref> and she permitted the nonprofit CoralWatch to use "Ocean Eyes" as part of an online awareness campaign about Australia's Great Barrier Reef.<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Kaufman |first=Gil |date=November 22, 2021 |title=Billie Eilish Teams With CoralWatch to Support Great Barrier Reef Conservation |url=https://www.billboard.com/music/pop/billie-eilish-coralwatch-great-barrier-reef-conservation-1235001247/ |url-status=live |magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211122144324/https://www.billboard.com/music/pop/billie-eilish-coralwatch-great-barrier-reef-conservation-1235001247/ |archive-date=November 22, 2021 |access-date=November 22, 2021}}</ref> Eilish was raised as a vegetarian, and became [[vegan]] in 2014. She is a regular advocate on social media for [[animal rights]] and [[veganism]], and has criticized the dairy,<ref name="finance.yahoo.com">{{cite web |date=February 19, 2020 |title=Is Billie Eilish Vegan? Plus 10 Other Celebs You Didn't Know Were Plant-Based |url=https://finance.yahoo.com/news/billie-eilish-vegan-plus-10-162800839.html |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210401025535/https://finance.yahoo.com/news/billie-eilish-vegan-plus-10-162800839.html |archive-date=April 1, 2021 |access-date=September 18, 2020 |publisher=[[Yahoo! Finance]]}}</ref> [[wool]],<ref>{{cite news |last1=Lewis |first1=Isobel |date=December 10, 2019 |title=Billie Eilish and Millie Bobby Brown honoured at PETA Awards |url=https://metro.co.uk/2019/12/10/billie-eilish-millie-bobby-brown-give-us-hope-future-teens-honoured-peta-11589114/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201123230028/https://metro.co.uk/2019/12/10/billie-eilish-millie-bobby-brown-give-us-hope-future-teens-honoured-peta-11589114/ |archive-date=November 23, 2020 |access-date=October 6, 2020 |newspaper=[[Metro (British newspaper)|Metro]]}}</ref> and [[mink]] fur industries.<ref>{{cite magazine |last1=Aubrey |first1=Elizabeth |date=October 21, 2019 |title=Billie Eilish says she's "disgusted" by people who wear mink fur |url=https://www.nme.com/news/music/billie-eilish-says-shes-disgusted-people-wear-mink-fur-2559267 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201009063021/https://www.nme.com/news/music/billie-eilish-says-shes-disgusted-people-wear-mink-fur-2559267 |archive-date=October 9, 2020 |access-date=October 6, 2020 |magazine=[[NME]]}}</ref> In 2023, Eilish stated she refuses to travel by private jet.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Wang |first=Jen |date=2023-01-04 |title=Billie Eilish on Climate Activism and Radical Hope |url=https://www.vogue.com/article/billie-eilish-climate-activism-january-cover-2022-video |access-date=2024-05-14 |website=Vogue |language=en-US |archive-date=April 30, 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240430173936/https://www.vogue.com/article/billie-eilish-climate-activism-january-cover-2022-video |url-status=live }}</ref>

Eilish has spoken in multiple occasions about [[women's rights]].<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Crone |first=Madeline |date=September 13, 2021 |title=2021 VMAs: Cyndi Lauper and Billie Eilish Turned VMAs Stage Into a Platform for Women's Rights |url=https://americansongwriter.com/2021-vmas-cyndi-lauper-and-billie-eilish-turned-vmas-stage-into-a-platform-for-womens-rights/ |access-date=August 28, 2022 |magazine=[[American Songwriter]] |archive-date=October 23, 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211023024036/https://americansongwriter.com/2021-vmas-cyndi-lauper-and-billie-eilish-turned-vmas-stage-into-a-platform-for-womens-rights/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last=Clark |first=Meredith |date=June 24, 2022 |title=Billie Eilish Explains Why She Referenced ''Depp vs Heard'' Trial in New Song |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/music/news/billie-eilish-roe-v-wade-abortion-b2109110.html |url-access=limited |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220723065914/https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/music/news/billie-eilish-roe-v-wade-abortion-b2109110.html |archive-date=July 23, 2022 |access-date=July 23, 2022 |newspaper=[[The Independent]]}}</ref> A supporter of [[body positivity]], she wrote and produced the 2020 short film ''[[Not My Responsibility]]'' as a response to [[body shaming]] toward her and the double standards placed upon women's appearances.<ref name="Uproxx">{{Cite web |last=Rossignol |first=Derrick |date=May 27, 2020 |title=Billie Eilish Shares Her Revealing Short Film, ''Not My Responsibility'' |url=https://uproxx.com/pop/billie-eilish-body-short-film-not-my-responsibility/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220422065628/https://uproxx.com/pop/billie-eilish-body-short-film-not-my-responsibility/ |archive-date=April 22, 2022 |access-date=July 11, 2022 |website=[[Uproxx]]}}</ref><ref name="Legaspi-2020">{{Cite magazine |last=Legaspi |first=Althea |date=May 27, 2020 |title=Billie Eilish Slams Body Shaming in Powerful ''Not My Responsibility'' Short Film |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/billie-eilish-not-my-responsibility-short-film-1005498/ |url-status=live |magazine=[[Rolling Stone]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201010114513/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/billie-eilish-not-my-responsibility-short-film-1005498/ |archive-date=October 10, 2020 |access-date=October 4, 2020 |url-access=limited}}</ref><ref name="Nesvig-2020">{{Cite magazine |last=Nesvig |first=Kara |date=May 27, 2020 |title=Billie Eilish Released the Full Version of ''Not My Responsibility'' |url=https://www.teenvogue.com/story/billie-eilish-not-my-responsibility-video |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200928230608/https://www.teenvogue.com/story/billie-eilish-not-my-responsibility-video |archive-date=September 28, 2020 |access-date=October 4, 2020 |magazine=[[Teen Vogue]]}}</ref> "[[Your Power]]", one of her 2021 singles, criticizes the sexual exploitation of young women, primarily by men who hold power over them.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Al-Heeti |first=Abrar |date=April 1, 2022 |title=Billie Eilish Happier Than Ever Tour Brings Catharsis, Camaraderie and Hope |url=https://www.cnet.com/culture/entertainment/billie-eilish-happier-than-ever-tour-brings-catharsis-camaraderie-and-hope/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220406062003/https://www.cnet.com/culture/entertainment/billie-eilish-happier-than-ever-tour-brings-catharsis-camaraderie-and-hope/ |archive-date=April 6, 2022 |access-date=July 18, 2022 |publisher=[[CNET]]}}</ref><ref name="Garner-2021">{{Cite magazine |last=Garner |first=Glenn |date=May 3, 2021 |title=Billie Eilish Says Every Woman She Knows Has Faced Sexual Misconduct: 'It's Everywhere' |url=https://people.com/music/billie-eilish-doesnt-know-one-woman-who-hasnt-faced-sexual-misconduct/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210913023342/https://people.com/music/billie-eilish-doesnt-know-one-woman-who-hasnt-faced-sexual-misconduct/ |archive-date=September 13, 2021 |access-date=July 18, 2022 |magazine=[[People (magazine)|People]]}}</ref> Eilish associates herself with the [[United States abortion-rights movement|US abortion rights movement]]; she expressed rage when Texas implemented [[Abortion in Texas|its anti-abortion laws]] in 2021.<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Carr |first=Debbie |date=October 4, 2021 |title=Billie Eilish condemns Texas anti-abortion laws during performance: "My body, my fucking choice" |url=https://www.nme.com/en_asia/news/music/billie-eilish-texas-abortion-law-austin-city-limits-my-body-my-fucking-choice-2021-3061808 |access-date=August 28, 2022 |magazine=[[NME]] |archive-date=May 14, 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220514042721/https://www.nme.com/en_asia/news/music/billie-eilish-texas-abortion-law-austin-city-limits-my-body-my-fucking-choice-2021-3061808 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |date=August 27, 2022 |title=Ariana Grande, Billie Eilish and Dua Lipa Back Abortion Rights Campaign |agency=[[BBC News]] |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/newsbeat-49482220 |access-date=August 28, 2022 |archive-date=August 15, 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220815134910/https://www.bbc.com/news/newsbeat-49482220 |url-status=live }}</ref> During the [[Glastonbury Festival 2022|2022 Glastonbury]] festival, she performed "Your Power" to condemn [[Dobbs v. Jackson Women's Health Organization|the overturning]] of ''[[Roe v. Wade]]''. She spoke of the decision: "Today is a really, really dark day for women in the U.S. I'm just going to say that as I cannot bear to think about it any longer in this moment."<ref>{{Cite news |date=July 13, 2022 |title=Phoebe Bridgers, Megan Fox, Jessica Chastain and more stars react to overturn of Roe v. Wade |url=https://www.usatoday.com/picture-gallery/entertainment/2022/06/27/roe-v-wade-overturn-celebrities-reactions-abortion/7744430001/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220730192704/https://www.usatoday.com/picture-gallery/entertainment/2022/06/27/roe-v-wade-overturn-celebrities-reactions-abortion/7744430001/ |archive-date=July 30, 2022 |access-date=July 30, 2022 |newspaper=[[USA Today]]}}</ref> She included a reference to ''Roe v. Wade''{{'s}} overturning in her 2022 track "TV", much of which she wrote after a draft of the court decision was leaked online in May.<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Sharf |first=Zack |date=June 24, 2022 |title=Billie Eilish Slams Internet for Caring About Depp-Heard Trial over Abortion Rights: 'Who Gives a F—?' |url=https://variety.com/2022/music/news/billie-eilish-johnny-depp-amber-heard-trial-1235302744/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220702134717/https://variety.com/2022/music/news/billie-eilish-johnny-depp-amber-heard-trial-1235302744/ |archive-date=July 2, 2022 |access-date=September 16, 2022 |magazine=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Legaspi |first=Althea |date=July 21, 2022 |title=Billie Eilish Drops Surprise ''Guitar Songs'' EP, Featuring Two New Songs |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/billie-eilish-guitar-songs-ep-1386276/ |url-status=live |magazine=[[Rolling Stone]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220721230712/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/billie-eilish-guitar-songs-ep-1386276/ |archive-date=July 21, 2022 |access-date=September 16, 2022 |url-access=limited}}</ref>

In March 2020, Eilish encouraged fans online to register to vote for the 2020 US presidential election.<ref>{{cite magazine |last=Neale |first=Matthew |date=March 6, 2020 |title=Billie Eilish is getting fans registered to vote for the US election |url=https://www.nme.com/news/music/billie-eilish-getting-fans-registered-to-vote-2621798 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201019234953/https://www.nme.com/news/music/billie-eilish-getting-fans-registered-to-vote-2621798 |archive-date=October 19, 2020 |access-date=October 6, 2020 |magazine=[[NME]]}}</ref> In August 2020, she performed at the [[2020 Democratic National Convention]] and announced her endorsement of [[Joe Biden 2020 presidential campaign|Joe Biden's presidential campaign]].<ref name="DNC">{{cite web |last1=Holcombe |first1=Madeline |title=Billie Eilish says to 'vote like our lives depend on it' in DNC performance |url=https://edition.cnn.com/2020/08/20/entertainment/billie-eilish-dnc-performance-my-future-trnd/index.html |website=[[CNN]] |access-date=October 15, 2020 |date=August 20, 2020 |archive-date=September 23, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200923180624/https://edition.cnn.com/2020/08/20/entertainment/billie-eilish-dnc-performance-my-future-trnd/index.html |url-status=live }}</ref>

In 2023, Eilish worked with others to start and fund REVERB's Music Decarbonization Project, and as part of a decarbonization project used solar powered stage lights.<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Havens |first=Lyndsey |date=2024-03-28 |title=Why Billie Eilish Insists on Sustainability In Her Career: 'It's a Never-Ending F–king Fight' |url=https://www.billboard.com/music/pop/billie-eilish-sustainability-eco-friendly-initiatives-mom-1235642455/ |access-date=2024-04-03 |magazine=Billboard |language=en-US |archive-date=April 3, 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240403161153/https://www.billboard.com/music/pop/billie-eilish-sustainability-eco-friendly-initiatives-mom-1235642455/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=REVERB {{!}} Music Decarbonization Project |url=https://reverb.org/campaign/music-decarbonization-project/ |access-date=2024-04-03 |website=REVERB |language=en |archive-date=April 1, 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240401043717/https://reverb.org/campaign/music-decarbonization-project/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

At the [[2024 Academy Awards]], Eilish wore an [[Artists4Ceasefire]] pin which calls for a ceasefire in the [[2023 Israel-Hamas war]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Oscars 2024: Protest pins worn on the red carpet and what they mean |url=https://www.bbc.com/culture/article/20240311-oscars-2024-artists-wear-protest-pins-ceasefire-equity-trans-children |access-date=2024-03-15 |website=www.bbc.com |archive-date=March 15, 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240315111516/https://www.bbc.com/culture/article/20240311-oscars-2024-artists-wear-protest-pins-ceasefire-equity-trans-children |url-status=live }}</ref>

== Personal life ==
Eilish lived with her parents in the [[Highland Park, Los Angeles|Highland Park]] neighborhood of Los Angeles until 2019, when she moved out.<ref name="Spanos-2021">{{Cite magazine|last=Spanos|first=Brittany|date=June 17, 2021|title=Billie Eilish and the Pursuit of Happiness|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-features/billie-eilish-new-album-happier-than-ever-tour-1183156/|access-date=July 21, 2021|magazine=[[Rolling Stone]]|archive-date=July 19, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210719000710/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-features/billie-eilish-new-album-happier-than-ever-tour-1183156/|url-status=live}}</ref> She said in 2021 that she still spends many nights in her childhood bedroom to be close to her parents.<ref name="Spanos-2021" /> She said she received a diagnosis of [[Tourette syndrome]] when she was 11;<ref>{{cite news |url= https://www.cnn.com/2022/05/23/entertainment/billie-eilish-tourette-syndrome/index.html |title= Billie Eilish finds having Tourette's syndrome 'exhausting' |first=Lisa |last=Respers France |date=May 23, 2022 |publisher= CNN |access-date=July 23, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230723111039/https://www.cnn.com/2022/05/23/entertainment/billie-eilish-tourette-syndrome/index.html |archive-date=July 23, 2023 |url-status=live}}</ref> and that she has [[synesthesia]]<ref>{{cite web|last1=Nattress|first1=Katrina|title=Billie Eilish Explains How Synesthesia Affects Her Music|url=https://www.iheart.com/content/2019-05-29-billie-eilish-explains-how-synesthesia-affects-her-music/|publisher=iHeartRadio|date=May 29, 2019|access-date=August 8, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191108140001/https://www.iheart.com/content/2019-05-29-billie-eilish-explains-how-synesthesia-affects-her-music/|archive-date=November 8, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> and has experienced [[Major depressive disorder|depression]].<ref>{{cite magazine|last=Trendell|first=Andrew|date=December 9, 2021|title=Billie Eilish on overcoming depression: "It's the most freeing feeling to be able to come out of that shell"|url=https://www.nme.com/news/music/billie-eilish-on-overcoming-depression-its-the-most-freeing-feeling-to-be-able-to-come-out-of-that-shell-2585202|access-date=July 21, 2021|magazine=[[NME]]|archive-date=July 21, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210721153918/https://www.nme.com/news/music/billie-eilish-on-overcoming-depression-its-the-most-freeing-feeling-to-be-able-to-come-out-of-that-shell-2585202|url-status=live}}</ref> Eilish has also shared that she experienced sexual abuse as a child.<ref name="Lee-2021">{{Cite magazine |last=Lee |first=Anna Grace |date=May 3, 2021 |title=Billie Eilish and the Importance of 'Your Power' |url=https://www.esquire.com/entertainment/music/a36317440/billie-eilish-your-power-body-image-lyrics-meaning-vogue-cover-interview/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220818031935/https://www.esquire.com/entertainment/music/a36317440/billie-eilish-your-power-body-image-lyrics-meaning-vogue-cover-interview/ |archive-date=August 18, 2022 |access-date=September 20, 2022 |magazine=[[Esquire (magazine)|Esquire]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |date=May 3, 2021 |title=Billie Eilish: Sexual Misconduct Is Everywhere |agency=[[BBC News]] |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/entertainment-arts-56969187 |url-status=live |access-date=November 18, 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221118185358/https://www.bbc.com/news/entertainment-arts-56969187 |archive-date=November 18, 2022}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last=Guy |first=Jack |date=May 3, 2021 |title=Billie Eilish on Exploitation and Not Letting Herself 'Be Owned Anymore' |url=https://www.cnn.com/style/article/billie-eilish-british-vogue-interview-scli-intl-gbr/index.html |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220809032410/https://edition.cnn.com/style/article/billie-eilish-british-vogue-interview-scli-intl-gbr/index.html |archive-date=August 9, 2022 |access-date=September 20, 2022 |agency=[[CNN]] }}</ref><ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Snapes |first=Laura |date=May 2, 2021 |title=Read Billie Eilish's ''Vogue'' Cover Interview in Full: 'It's All About What Makes You Feel Good' |url=https://www.vogue.co.uk/news/article/billie-eilish-vogue-interview |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210729145117/https://www.vogue.co.uk/news/article/billie-eilish-vogue-interview |archive-date=July 29, 2021 |access-date=July 30, 2021 |magazine=[[British Vogue]]}}</ref>

Eilish previously dated rapper Brandon Adams, who goes by the stage name 7:AMP.<ref>{{cite web|last=Mauch|first=Ally|url=https://people.com/music/billie-eilish-opens-up-about-split-from-ex-boyfriend/|title=Billie Eilish Opens Up About Her Split from Ex-Boyfriend Q: 'I Just Wasn't Happy'|work=People|date=February 27, 2021|accessdate=June 17, 2021|archive-date=June 18, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210618121652/https://people.com/music/billie-eilish-opens-up-about-split-from-ex-boyfriend/|url-status=live}}</ref> She dated singer [[Jesse Rutherford (singer)|Jesse Rutherford]] from October 2022 to May 2023.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.complex.com/music/billie-eilish-jesse-rutherford-age-gap-halloween-costumes|title=Billie Eilish and Boyfriend Jesse Rutherford Use Halloween Costumes to Poke Fun at Age Gap|last1=Martinez|first1=Jose|magazine=Complex|quote=Billie Eilish and Jesse Rutherford decided to respond to the public discourse surrounding their 11-year age difference with their Halloween costumes. Eilish dressed up as a baby, complete with a bonnet and diaper, and Rutherford donned a bald cap with grey hair.|date=October 31, 2022|access-date=November 1, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230227145751/https://www.complex.com/music/billie-eilish-jesse-rutherford-age-gap-halloween-costumes|archive-date=February 27, 2023|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine | last1=Irvin|first1=Jack|last2=Tracy|first2=Brianne|url=https://people.com/music/billie-eilish-jesse-rutherford-break-up-split/ | title=Billie Eilish and Jesse Rutherford Break up After Less Than a Year as Rep Says They 'Remain Good Friends'|magazine=[[People (magazine)|People]]|date=May 17, 2023|accessdate=August 31, 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231002141627/https://people.com/music/billie-eilish-jesse-rutherford-break-up-split/|archive-date=October 2, 2023|url-status=live}}</ref> She has said that she is attracted to both men and women.<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Stephan |first=Katcy |date=November 13, 2023 |title=Billie Eilish Was Made for This: 'Being a Woman Is Just Such a War, Forever' |url=https://variety.com/2023/music/features/billie-eilish-body-shamers-sexualized-barbie-oscar-buzz-1235787860/ |access-date=November 13, 2023 |magazine=Variety |archive-date=November 13, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231113203041/https://variety.com/2023/music/features/billie-eilish-body-shamers-sexualized-barbie-oscar-buzz-1235787860/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last=Fears |first=Danika |date=December 4, 2023 |title=Billie Eilish Accuses Variety of 'Outing' Her on Red Carpet |work=The Daily Beast |url=https://www.thedailybeast.com/billie-eilish-accuses-variety-of-outing-her-on-red-carpet |access-date=December 4, 2023 |archive-date=December 12, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231212035522/https://www.thedailybeast.com/billie-eilish-accuses-variety-of-outing-her-on-red-carpet |url-status=live }}</ref>

Billie Eilish is an [[agnostic]].<ref>{{cite web | url=https://people.com/music/billie-eilish-was-super-religious-even-though-family-wasnt/ | title=Billie Eilish Reveals She Was Once 'Super Religious' Even Though Her Family Wasn't: 'It Was Weird'|work=People|date=July 20, 2020|last=Harmata|first=Claudia}}</ref> In 2023, she [[came out]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Specter |first=Emma |date=2024-05-17 |title=Billie Eilish, Welcome to the Queer-Pop-Girlie Canon |url=https://www.vogue.com/article/billie-eilish-queer-pop-girlie-canon |access-date=2024-05-27 |website=Vogue |language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Thompson |first=Jaden |date=2023-12-02 |title=Billie Eilish on Coming Out: ‘I Didn’t Realize People Didn’t Know’ |url=https://variety.com/2023/music/news/billie-eilish-coming-out-hitmakers-1235818929/ |access-date=2024-05-27 |website=Variety |language=en-US}}</ref>

